actions.prompt:
Draft a personalized outreach message. Generic messages get ignored; specific messages anchored in real history get replies. The draft must contain:

  1. A CONCRETE ANCHOR — one specific reference pulled from the actual timeline / profile below (a past visit, a service used, a topic discussed, a product they bought). NEVER invent. If the timeline is empty, use the profile (their name, where you met them, the segment they're in) and stay honest about it being a first touch.

  2. A CLEAR REASON FOR WRITING — the recipient should understand within one line why this message exists right now (their birthday, a new offer relevant to their last purchase, a follow-up to a recent visit, a check-in cadence). Tie it to the occasion below.

  3. A SINGLE LOW-EFFORT NEXT STEP — one concrete action they can take. "Reply with a date that works" beats "let me know when you have time". "Use code SUMMER for 15% off this week" beats "check out our offers". For pure check-ins where no action is wanted, end on a warm but specific note about them — not a bromide.

Length: 3-5 sentences. Human, not corporate. Match the tone of past interactions if visible. No filler openers ("Hope you're well", "Long time no talk", "Just wanted to reach out"). No closers like "Looking forward to hearing from you."

Occasion: {{occasion}}
Extra context: {{context}}

Contact + timeline:
{{_DATA}}

Write ONLY the message body. No subject line, no signature, no meta-commentary, no quote marks.
